questions.question:
A process executes the code
fork();
fork();
fork();
The total number of child processes created is
A. 3
B. 4
C. 7
D. 8

The following C program is executed on a Unix/Linux system:
#include<unistd.h>
int main() {
    int i;
    for(i=0; i<10; i++)
        if(i%2 == 0) fork();
    return 0;
}
The total number of child processes created is ___________

Consider the following code snippet using the fork() and wait() system calls. Assume that the code compiles and runs correctly, and that the system calls run successfully without any errors.
int x = 3;
while(x > 0) {
    fork();
    printf("hello");
    wait(NULL);
    x--;
}
The total number of times the printf statement is executed is ___________
A. 6
B. 7
C. 8
D. Unbounded
